verses.text:
The peace that once I felt there, Will nev-er be for-got-ten;
The glow-ing love that filled my heart, The joy that made it bright-en;
The words of truth that touched my soul, The songs of praise a-scend-ing.

My teach-er's voice I hear a-gain, So gen-tle and so kind;
The les-sons that she used to teach, Come fresh-ly to my mind;
The pray-ers she breathed for me, The coun-sel true and ten-der.

Though years have passed since then a-way, And I am far from home;
Yet still I love that sa-cred place, Where first I learned to pray;
And when life's toils and cares are o'er, And I shall go to rest.
